"623","SCHEDULE A"
"624","The following text replaces the section of each fund's prospectus titled"
"625","Exchanging shares:"
"626","Exchanging shares"
"627","Generally You may exchange shares of the fund for the same class of shares"
"628","of other funds sold by the distributor. For investors who qualify as Clients"
"629","of Eligible Financial Intermediaries and participate in Eligible Investment"
"630","Programs made available through their financial intermediaries (such as"
"631","investors in fee-based advisory or mutual fund wrap programs), an exchange"
"632","may be made from Class A or Class C shares to Class I shares of the same fund"
"633","under certain limited circumstances. Please refer to the section of this"
"634","prospectus titled Retirement and Institutional Investors - eligible
investors or contact your financial intermediary for more information. An"
"635","exchange of shares of one fund for shares of another fund is considered a sale"
"636","and generally results in a capital gain or loss for federal income tax"
"637","purposes, unless you are investing through an IRA, 401(k) or other tax-"
"638","advantaged account. An exchange of shares of one class directly for shares of"
"639","another class of the same fund normally should not be taxable for federal"
"640","income tax purposes. You should talk to your tax advisor before making an"
"641","exchange. The exchange privilege is not intended as a vehicle for short-term"
"642","trading. The fund may suspend or terminate your exchange privilege if you"
"643","engage in a pattern of excessive exchanges."
"644","Legg Mason offers a distinctive family of funds tailored to help meet"
"645","the varying needs of large and small investors"
"646","You may exchange shares at their net asset value next determined after receipt"
"647","by your Service Agent or the transfer agent of your exchange request in good"
"648","order.  If you bought shares through a Service Agent, contact your Service"
"649","Agent to learn which funds your Service Agent makes available to you for"
"650","exchanges  If you bought shares directly from the fund, contact the fund at"
"651","1-877-721-1926 tolearn which funds are available to you for exchanges"
"652","Exchanges may be made only between accounts that have identical registrations"
"653","Not all funds offer all classes"
"654","Funds that offer Class B shares will continue to make them"
"655","available for incoming exchanges after July 1, 2011"
"656","Some funds are offered only in a limited number of states."
"657","Your Service Agent or the fund will provide information about the funds"
"658","offered in your state"
"659","Always be sure to read the prospectus of the fund into which you are"
"660","exchanging shares."
"661","Investment minimums, sales charges and other requirements"
"662"," In most instances, your shares will not be subject to an initial sales"
"663","charge or acontingent deferred sales charge at the time of the exchange"
"664"," Your contingent deferred sales charge (if any) will continue to be measured"
"665","from the date of your original purchase of shares subject to a contingent"
"666","deferred sales charge,and you will be subject to the contingent deferred sales"
"667","charge of the fund that you originally purchased"
"668"," You will generally be required to meet the minimum investment requirement"
"669","for the class of shares of the fund or share class into which your exchange is"
"670","made (except in the case of systematic exchange plans)"
"671"," Your exchange will also be subject to any other requirements of the fund or"
"672","share class into which you are exchanging shares"
"673"," If you hold share certificates, you must deliver the certificates, endorsed"
"674","for transfer or with signed stock powers, to the transfer agent or your"
"675","Service Agent before the exchange is effective"
"676"," The fund may suspend or terminate your exchange privilege if you engage in a"
"677","pattern of excessive exchanges"
"678","By telephone Contact your Service Agent or, if you hold shares directly with"
"679","the fund, call the fund at 1-877-721-1926 between 8:00 a.m. and 5:30 p.m."
"680","(Eastern time) for information. Exchanges are priced at the net asset value"
"681","next determined."
"682","By mail Contact your Service Agent or, if you hold shares directly with the"
"683","fund, write to the fund at the following address:"
"684","Legg Mason Funds"
"685","P.O. Box 55214"
"686","Boston, Massachusetts 02205-8504"
"687","Through a systematic exchange plan"
"688","You may be permitted to schedule automatic exchanges of shares of the fund for"
"689","shares of other funds available for exchange. All requirements for exchanging"
"690","shares described above apply to these exchanges. In addition:"
"691"," Exchanges may be made monthly, every alternate month, quarterly, semi-"
"692","annually or annually"
"693"," Each exchange must meet the applicable investment minimums for systematic"
"694","investment plans (see Purchase and sale of fund shares)"
"695","For more information, please contact your Service Agent or the fund or consult"
"696","the SAI."
